    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. but what about people who argue that without some level of national identity, you can't really have the trust needed for things like social safety nets or even just basic civic participation? isn't there a connection between feeling part of a nation and actually wanting to support your fellow citizens?",
